The paper deals with distributed broadcasting in multiple-access channels, which is a topic related to information theory and networking. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the study of algorithms and their performance, which falls under the scope of cs.AL (Algorithms). Additionally, the paper deals with the analysis of queue size and packet latency, which are related to distributed computing and distributed systems, respectively, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely sub-categories as well.
